🔴 **Tool Issue** — `OperationsDiscovery.properties?: any`

The `properties` field was previously typed as `Record<string, unknown>` in v5.3.0 but is now typed as `any` in this modular migration. This weakens type safety for consumers and is a regression.

**Before (v5.3.0):**
```ts
export interface OperationsDiscovery {
    display?: Display;
    name?: string;
    origin?: string;
    properties?: Record<string, unknown>;
}
```

**After (v6.0.0-beta.1):**
```ts
export interface OperationsDiscovery {
    display?: Display;
    name?: string;
    origin?: string;
    properties?: any;
}
```

**Fix:** Please report this regression to the [autorest.typescript generation tool](https://github.com/Azure/autorest.typescript/issues) so the modular generator emits `Record<string, unknown>` instead of `any` for untyped properties objects.

🔴 **Tool Issue** — `ErrorAdditionalInfo.info?: any`

The `info` field was previously typed as `Record<string, unknown>` in v5.3.0 but is now typed as `any` in this modular migration. Using `any` weakens type safety for consumers and is a regression.

**Before (v5.3.0):**
```ts
export interface ErrorAdditionalInfo {
    readonly info?: Record<string, unknown>;
    readonly type?: string;
}
```

**After (v6.0.0-beta.1):**
```ts
export interface ErrorAdditionalInfo {
    readonly info?: any;
    readonly type?: string;
}
```

**Fix:** Please report this regression to the [autorest.typescript generation tool](https://github.com/Azure/autorest.typescript/issues) so the modular generator emits `Record<string, unknown>` instead of `any` for this standard ARM error type.
